5:
Was the seminar NOT supposed to
be just the three of us?
14:
Sorry... I didn't want it to turn into a
huge thing either, but...
19:
So you're gonna take these kids
adventuring, keep lesson logs, and
eventually, compile everything into
a book. If that doesn't turn a profit,
then I don't know business!
23:
Right?! So, um... If you don't mind, I'd
like to set aside some time for my
seminar...
26:
Oh, of course, of course. But before
that, we best find a few more
interested participants.
29:
Wait, what? Shouldn't we keep it to
two? We can't have a crowd just
stampeding around. Someone
could get hurt.
32:
You know what's gonna get people
hurt? If you go around playing
favorites like that. Nuh-uh. You're
bringing more fans along.
34:
We'll plan a two-day tour. The kids
you mentioned before can be
security. The remaining spots will be
raffled off. Ooh, how about making
the lotto tickets a bonus for buying
your new book?
37:
So they have to buy both? Mm... Do
you think we could be a little nicer to
the fans?
40:
Your wish is my command! The
tickets will be sold separately!
45:
Levy, you're not good at saying no,
are you?
49:
He's not a bad person. He's just a
really GOOD entrepreneur.
52:
But anyways, the point is, I'm sorry.
This totally isn't what you signed up
for.
57:
I don't mind. It's fun to travel with
new friends.
60:
Gosh, I'm so embarrassed though. I
never imagined you guys were
adventuring between worlds. Like,
what could I possibly teach you?
64:
According to Light, we "yet have
much to learn."
70:
Well, I better get this show on the
road.

Hi, everyone! Gather round!
78:
We're not missing anyone, are
we?

Okay. Then let's begin. This is
Kaleidoscope Trawling 101, taught by
yours truly... Levy Grace!
82: She sure knows how to work a crowd.
90:
The first thing you've got to do is
observe the enemy. That's how you
figure out what tactics to use, or
whether you should stand your
ground or run.
95:
Oh, look! This is the perfect chance
to train those eyes. Who can tell me
how to deal with that monster?
100:
We're just dainty little flowers!
Protect us with your glamorous
swordplay, queen!
103:
Um... This guy's seriously small-fry.
I'm pretty sure you can take—
110: Next, it's your turn. Impress me.
117:
I'm so sorry... That was a total waste
of your time.
121:
Your fans greatly admire how you
are portrayed in books.
125:
You can say that again. They want
to the see the strong, badass,
glamorous Levy Grace.
127:
But that's not who I am. I'm just a
normal adventurer who wants to go
places.
130:
I want to explore the depths of the
Kaleidoscope, just like my heroes.
Even if that means messing up or
looking dumb or not showering for a
month.
134:
What do I do? Give up on my
dreams and live the life of a fairytale
hero? Or follow my dreams and
treat my fans to a rude awakening?
135: That's not a choice I want to make.
139:
Are your fans' expectations a
burden?
145:
No, I... I like seeing them happy.
Otherwise, I wouldn't even be trying
this hard.
150:
Why does it have to be a choice?
Why can't you have both?
155:
Is that even possible? You saw what
happened earlier.
160:
Anything is possible. You just have
to keep trying.
164:
You know what? You're right. Why
am I giving up before giving it my all?
168:
This tour's still got a day left.
Tomorrow, I'm gonna teach you all
how to REALLY adventure—in style!
